    Let tt be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If tt is equal to TOKEN_PUBLIC from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
    Otherwise:
        If tt is equal to TOKEN_PRIVATE from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
        Otherwise:
            If tt is equal to TOKEN_PROTECTED from Lexer:
                proc advance_token with parser
            End If
        End If
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Interface declaration: 'interface Name [extends I1, I2, ...] { members }'.
Interfaces support multiple extends. Members are parsed with the shared
class-member parser (which handles method signatures and constants); properties
are syntactically accepted but semantically rejected downstream.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_interface" takes parser as Integer, attrs as Integer returns Integer:
