@Reasoning:
Trait declaration: 'trait Name { members }'. Structurally identical to a class
body (properties, methods, constants, nested trait-use) but without
extends/implements.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_trait" takes parser as Integer, attrs as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a trait declaration

    proc advance_token with parser            Note: 'trait'

    Let node be proc create_ast_node with "trait"
    proc set_ast_attribute with node, "attributes", attrs

    Let name be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
    proc set_ast_attribute with node, "name", name
    proc advance_token with parser

    Let members be proc list_create from ListOps
    proc set_ast_attribute with node, "members", members
    proc parse_class_body with parser, members

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Enum declaration (PHP 8.1): 'enum Name [: backingType] [implements ...] { cases
and members }'. Cases are 'case Name [= value];'. Methods and constants may also
